{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% set nav = 'standard' %}

{% block title %}A shared members' transparency standard · RHT Members' Transparency Circle{% endblock %}
{% block description %}A common set of questions any beneficiary can put to their own community, and that the Circle puts together to the treaty-wide fund. One standard, used everywhere.{% endblock %}

{% block hero %}
<section class="hero">
  <div class="wrap wrap--wide">
    <p class="eyebrow">One standard, used everywhere</p>
    <h1>A shared members' transparency standard.</h1>
    <p class="lead">A common set of questions any member can put to their own community, and that we can put together to the treaty-wide fund. The point is one standard, used everywhere, so no member is asking alone and every community is held to the same openness.</p>
    <p class="lead"><strong>These are questions, not accusations.</strong> Asking to see how our settlement is governed is our right as beneficiaries.</p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <h2>Part 1: Treaty-wide</h2>
  <p>To the Robinson Huron Treaty Litigation Fund.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>The compensation and disbursement agreement that controls how the settlement is shared, in full.</li>
    <li>The current list of trustees, how each is chosen, and the length of their terms.</li>
    <li>The process for amending the agreement, including the threshold required, and a record of any amendments made to date.</li>
    <li>What financial reporting beneficiaries receive about the fund, and how often.</li>
    <li>How decisions are made about what is shared collectively versus paid to individuals, and how members have a say in those decisions.</li>
    <li>The contact and process for a member to ask questions or raise concerns.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Part 2: In each community</h2>
  <p>To your own Chief and Council.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Who holds the community's settlement funds (the institution and the trustee), and where they are kept.</li>
    <li>The trust's governing rules (the indenture): what the funds can be invested in, the conflict-of-interest rules binding the trustee and anyone who can move money, and how the trustee is paid.</li>
    <li>Who can authorize a withdrawal from the trust, and what approvals are required before money is released.</li>
    <li>How the held funds reconcile to the community's audited financial statements, so members can see where each piece sits.</li>
    <li>What reporting members receive about the trust, and how often.</li>
    <li>For any portion held for minors or for specific community purposes: the terms, and when and how it is released.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="card card--magenta">
    <h3>How to use this</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Members in any community can send Part 2 to their own Chief and Council as a plain request for information.</li>
      <li>The Circle sends Part 1 together to the treaty-wide fund as one voice.</li>
      <li>Share what you receive back. Transparency answers help every community, and silence tells its own story.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="btn-row">
    <a class="btn" href="/get-involved">Get the one-page version</a>
    <a class="btn btn--alt" href="/communities">See it run in a community</a>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
